push the head back?

513
00:29:29,019 --> 00:29:30,687
Megan!

514
00:29:36,485 --> 00:29:38,612
What do you think it is?

515
00:29:42,699 --> 00:29:44,618
It's a ghost ball.

516
00:30:00,509 --> 00:30:03,095
I think it wants
us to follow it.

517
00:30:04,513 --> 00:30:06,682
I think you're crazy.

518
00:30:13,397 --> 00:30:16,483
It does. It wants
us to follow it.

519
00:30:31,790 --> 00:30:33,500
Hey, Megan, wait up!

520
00:30:39,798 --> 00:30:43,010
Where's that scary
albino when you need him?

521
00:30:49,308 --> 00:30:51,393
Oh. Hello.

522
00:30:52,603 --> 00:30:55,189
Have you seen my husband?

523
00:30:59,610 --> 00:31:01,320
Excuse me.

524
00:31:02,196 --> 00:31:03,989
Wait!

525
00:31:04,990 --> 00:31:06,491
Wait!

526
00:31:25,093 --> 00:31:27,221
Oh, Ramsley. It's you.

527
00:31:27,304 --> 00:31:28,597
May I help you?

528
00:31:28,639 --> 00:31:29,681
Yes.

529
00:31:29,806 --> 00:31:31,683
I was just looking
for my husband.

530
00:31:31,808 --> 00:31:33,852
Ah, indeed.

531
00:31:33,894 --> 00:31:36,605
I left him in the library.

532
00:31:36,688 --> 00:31:39,191
Right through there.

533
00:31:41,318 --> 00:31:44,613
Honey, it's late. Let's
not fight anymore.

534
00:31:44,696 --> 00:31:46,573
Come to bed?

535
00:31:46,657 --> 00:31:48,492
Oh! I'm sorry.

536
00:31:48,617 --> 00:31:49,993
I thought you were my husband.

537
00:31:50,118 --> 00:31:51,245
Can I help you with that?

538
00:31:51,286 --> 00:31:53,914
Ramsley hates it when I
leave things lying about.

539
00:31:53,997 --> 00:31:56,250
Yes. He seems a bit proper.

540
00:31:56,291 --> 00:31:58,502
He strikes most people that way.

541
00:31:58,585 --> 00:32:01,296
Once you get to know him,
you'll find that's not the case.

542
00:32:01,338 --> 00:32:03,715
But he's really...

543
00:32:05,592 --> 00:32:07,719
He's really very sweet.

544
00:32:07,761 --> 00:32:09,346
Thank you.

545
00:32:09,388 --> 00:32:11,306
He's been like a father to me.

546
00:32:11,390 --> 00:32:15,185
Mr. Gracey, may I
ask you something?

547
00:32:15,310 --> 00:32:18,188
Yes. Of course. Anything.

548
00:32:18,313 --> 00:32:19,398
This house.

549
00:32:19,481 --> 00:32:21,817
It's been in your
family for generations.

550
00:32:21,859 --> 00:32:24,319
It's your home.

551
00:32:24,403 --> 00:32:26,780
Why do you want to sell it?

552
00:32:28,198 --> 00:32:32,995
These walls are filled
with so many memories.

553
00:32:33,036 --> 00:32:37,291
Some of them painful.

554
00:32:39,793 --> 00:32:44,214
I think for you to understand,
I really must show you.

555
00:32:45,716 --> 00:32:49,303
It's all right. There's
nothing to be afraid of.

556
00:32:52,306 --> 00:32:54,099
Although it might be
a bit worn and faded

557
00:32:54,183 --> 00:32:55,893
from its original grandeur,

558
00:32:56,018 --> 00:32:59,104
this house was once filled
with so many things.

559
00:32:59,188 --> 00:33:00,689
So much life.

560
00:33:00,814 --> 00:33:06,612
With grand parties, dancing,
laughter, and, above all, hope.

561
00:33:06,653 --> 00:33:09,406
Being a Gracey meant that
you were denied nothing.

562
00:33:09,489 --> 00:33:11,200
The world was yours.

563
00:33:11,283 --> 00:33:14,203
What happened here, Mr. Gracey?

564
00:33:14,244 --> 00:33:15,287
She did.

565
00:33:15,412 --> 00:33:17,414
Who?

566
00:33:17,497 --> 00:33:19,249
Elizabeth.

567
00:33:19,291 --> 00:33:23,212
Hers is the story that
haunts these walls.

568
00:33:48,195 --> 00:33:49,988
Come on.

569
00:33:50,113 --> 00:33:52,199
Megan, wait.

570
00:33:52,282 --> 00:33:55,536
You don't know the last time
that thing's been inspected.

571
00:33:55,577 --> 00:33:58,789
Would you just relax? Where's
your sense of adventure?

572
00:34:09,883 --> 00:34:12,094
This is against all
my better judgment.

573
00:34:45,586 --> 00:34:47,504
Hi!

574
00:34:52,009 --> 00:34:54,011
Is anyone home?

575
00:35:13,697 --> 00:35:16,491
Those must be termites.

576
00:35:18,493 --> 00:35:20,579
Some big-ass termites.
That's all.

577
00:36:19,179 --> 00:36:21,098
Hello?

578
00:36:37,197 --> 00:36:38,407
- Oh!

579
00:36:38,448 --> 00:36:39,616
Oh.

580
00:36:40,909 --> 00:36:44,079
Aah! Aah!

581
00:37:15,319 --> 00:37:16,904
Megan!

582
00:37:23,493 --> 00:37:25,412
Mom.

583
00:37:25,495 --> 00:37:27,789
What are you doing here?
You're not supposed to be here!

584
00:37:27,915 --> 00:37:30,417
This is unspeakable! Unspeakable!
You have to leave!

585
00:37:30,501 --> 00:37:33,212
- Who is that?
- That's none of your business.

586
00:37:33,295 --> 00:37:35,589
Now, come on. Get out of here.
It's way past your bedtime.

587
00:37:35,714 --> 00:37:36,882
Her name was Elizabeth.

588
00:37:37,007 --> 00:37:39,218
Are you kids hungry? Does
anybody want a cookie?

589
00:37:39,259 --> 00:37:40,594
Cookies?!

590
00:37:40,719 --> 00:37:43,180
Don't offer them cookies!
They're trespassers!

591
00:37:43,222 --> 00:37:45,390
Trespassers don't get cookies!

592
00:37:45,516 --> 00:37:47,017
This is none of their concern.

593
00:37:47,100 --> 00:37:48,894
It is their concern!
They're involved!

594
00:37:51,188 --> 00:37:53,190
Hide! Hide!

595
00:38:04,618 --> 00:38:07,996
The children are
not in their room.

596
00:38:08,080 --> 00:38:09,456
Have you seen them?

597
00:38:09,498 --> 00:38:11,291
Children? What children?

598
00:38:11,333 --> 00:38:13,919
What children?

599
00:38:20,008 --> 00:38:21,385
Her children.

600
00:38:21,510 --> 00:38:24,888
The children she wasn't
supposed to bring.

601
00:38:25,013 --> 00:38:28,684
Along with that brainless
husband of hers.

602
00:38:29,518 --> 00:38:31,019
Thank you.

603
00:38:38,694 --> 00:38:40,612
If I had to listen
to another word

604
00:38:40,696 --> 00:38:44,199
from that insufferable fool,
I think I would have burst.

605
00:38:44,241 --> 00:38:47,286
Of course, sir. What a fool!

606
00:38:47,411 --> 00:38:49,538
Did I not tell
her to come alone?

607
00:38:49,580 --> 00:38:52,708
Is it really too much to ask
for a little cooperation?

608
00:38:52,791 --> 00:38:53,792
A little order?

609
00:38:53,917 --> 00:38:56,086
Of course not, sir.

610
00:38:56,211 --> 00:39:00,299
If you find the children,
bring them to me.

611
00:39:00,382 --> 00:39:01,800
- Certainly, sir.
- Yes, sir.

612
00:39:01,884 --> 00:39:04,678
The final arrangements
have been made.

613
00:39:04,720 --> 00:39:08,390
Nothing further will interfere
with the master's plan.

614
00:39:18,817 --> 00:39:22,196
Thank God I heard your voice.
I lost my way.

615
00:39:22,321 --> 00:39:23,722
I don't know how
to get out of here.

616
00:39:23,746 --> 00:39:25,490
I'm sorry if I sound
a little frazzled.

617
00:39:25,616 --> 00:39:27,993
I just had myself a little
freak show back there.

618
00:39:28,118 --> 00:39:29,870
It's time to respond.

619
00:39:29,912 --> 00:39:31,705
I was supposed to
meet with Mr. Gracey.

620
00:39:31,788 --> 00:39:34,166
But I got stuck in the wall.

621
00:39:34,208 --> 00:39:37,711
Goblins and ghoulies
from last Halloween,

622
00:39:37,753 --> 00:39:41,215
awaken the spirits
with your tambourine.

623
00:39:41,298 --> 00:39:44,092
Okay, I hear you, but I don't see you.
Where are you?

624
00:39:44,218 --> 00:39:50,390
I am Madame Leota, seer of
all, voice to the spirits.

625
00:39:50,516 --> 00:39:52,809
Whom do you seek?

626
00:39:55,187 --> 00:39:56,688
Hey! Hey!

627
00:39:56,813 --> 00:39:57,981
Hey, let me out of here!

628
00:39:58,106 --> 00:40:00,484
Silence! Whom do you seek?

629
00:40:00,609 --> 00:40:02,402
I am seeking a way out of here.

630
00:40:02,486 --> 00:40:04,112
Then you must look within.

631
00:40:04,196 --> 00:40:06,236
I don't want to look within.
I want to look without.

632
00:40:06,260 --> 00:40:07,699
There is great
evil in this house.

633
00:40:07,783 --> 00:40:09,993
A devil's curse. It
seeks to destroy you.

634
00:40:10,035 --> 00:40:12,204
Why would something
seek to destroy me?

635
00:40:12,246 --> 00:40:13,539
I'm just here to sell the house.

636
00:40:13,580 --> 00:40:17,000
Dark spirits from the
grave, come forth.

637
00:40:17,084 --> 00:40:20,420
Lift us from the
black and show us.

638
00:40:20,504 --> 00:40:22,339
Show us the way back.

639
00:40:22,381 --> 00:40:24,216
Dark spirits? Hey,
no dark spirits.

640
00:40:24,299 --> 00:40:25,859
Don't you make no
dark spirits come out.

641
00:40:25,883 --> 00:40:28,679
Lift us. Lift us
up to the light.

642
00:40:28,804 --> 00:40:31,682
And lead us through
this stormy night.

643
00:40:31,723 --> 00:40:34,017
Hey, hey, hey. Hey!

644
00:40:34,101 --> 00:40:36,186
Hey, I'd really like
to stay on the ground.

645
00:40:36,311 --> 00:40:38,511
I'd rather stay on the ground.
Can I stay on the ground?

646
00:40:38,535 --> 00:40:41,483
Evil and darkness have
fallen this night.

647
00:40:41,608 --> 00:40:44,903
But now to survive, you
must gain new sight.

648
00:40:44,987 --> 00:40:46,613
I must first gain new underwear.

649
00:40:46,697 --> 00:40:49,116
Only the light
will lead the way.

650
00:40:49,199 --> 00:40:51,493
Follow it and find
your way home.

651
00:40:51,618 --> 00:40:54,997
There's no place like home.
There's no place like home.

652
00:40:55,080 --> 00:40:57,875
Go, Mr. Evers. Your
family is at stake.

653
00:40:57,916 --> 00:41:01,295
Your very life is at stake.
Break the curse.

654
00:41:01,420 --> 00:41:04,298
There is no escape for you
unless you lift this spell.

655
00:41:04,381 --> 00:41:06,091
Go. Save yourself.

656
00:41:06,216 --> 00:41:07,843
Save your family.

657
00:41:07,885 --> 00:41:10,804
Release her. Release us all!

658
00:41:10,888 --> 00:41:13,098
I'm getting so queasy.
I'm getting very queasy.

659
00:41:20,314 --> 00:41:22,191
Oh!

660
00:41:27,613 --> 00:41:31,408
Aah! Aah!

661
00:41:48,300 --> 00:41:50,219
Aah! Aah!

662
00:41:51,595 --> 00:41:53,805
Aah!

663
00:41:59,394 --> 00:42:00,812
Oh!

664
00:42:07,110 --> 00:42:08,820
- Dad!
- Dad!

665
00:42:08,904 --> 00:42:10,489
Hey! Michael and
Megan, you okay?

666
00:42:10,614 --> 00:42:11,740
We're fine, thanks.

667
00:42:11,782 --> 00:42:13,492
Get your things.
Let's get out of here.

668
00:42:13,617 --> 00:42:14,493
We have a problem.

669
00:42:14,618 --> 00:42:16,578
Because of the rain? We're
gonna get a little wet.

670
00:42:16,703 --> 00:42:18,705
Let's just find your
mom and get out of here.

671
00:42:18,789 --> 00:42:21,291
I'm afraid that's not possible.
She can't leave.

672
00:42:21,416 --> 00:42:22,417
And why not?

673
00:42:22,478 --> 00:42:23,478
Because she can't!

674
00:42:23,502 --> 00:42:27,005
If I could tell you, I would.
But I can't, so I won't, okay?

675
00:42:27,047 --> 00:42:28,715
Hey, how'd you...

676
00:42:29,568 --> 00:42:30,568
Hey, look. Come on.

677
00:42:30,592 --> 00:42:32,719
Daddy's having more hallucinations.
Let's go.

678
00:42:32,803 --> 00:42:34,596
- They're ghosts, Dad.
- They're not ghosts.

679
00:42:34,680 --> 00:42:37,015
We're just having hallucinations
from that dinner we ate.

680
00:42:37,099 --> 00:42:39,184
It was that chicken.
It didn't taste right.

681
00:42:39,309 --> 00:42:40,561
- Oh!
- It's not the chicken!

682
00:42:40,602 --> 00:42:43,105
All right. It's not the chicken.
But we're getting out of here.

683
00:42:43,146 --> 00:42:44,398
But we have to help them.

684
00:42:44,481 --> 00:42:47,484
You can't help the dead, honey.
They're beyond help.

685
00:42:47,609 --> 00:42:48,861
The man's talking sense.

686
00:42:48,902 --> 00:42:51,405
Everyone should keep their
noses in their own business.

687
00:42:51,488 --> 00:42:53,282
But we have to help
them break the curse.

688
00:42:53,407 --> 00:42:55,200
Why is everybody
talking about a curse?

689
00:42:55,284 --> 00:42:57,494
Have you been talking to
that crazy green gypsy

690
00:42:57,619 --> 00:42:58,704
in the giant paperweight?

691
00:42:58,787 --> 00:43:00,414
We've got to go back to see her.

692
00:43:00,497 --> 00:43:02,624
- No back. I'm not going back.
- But, Dad!

693
00:43:02,708 --> 00:43:04,793
They had me floating
all around the room.

694
00:43:04,918 --> 00:43:06,545
Hey, I was strapped to a chair,

695
00:43:06,587 --> 00:43:08,827
floating around the room with
a marching band chasing me.

696
00:43:08,952 --> 00:43:10,792
I'm not going back anywhere!
Forget it, Casper!

697
00:43:10,816 --> 00:43:12,593
But Mom's in trouble.

698
00:43:12,718 --> 00:43:14,303
What kind of trouble?

699
00:43:26,899 --> 00:43:31,695
She died here in this house.

700
00:43:31,737 --> 00:43:34,114
She was so very young.

701
00:43:34,198 --> 00:43:37,492
So very beautiful.

702
00:43:37,618 --> 00:43:41,496
She was in love with the
heir to this mansion.

703
00:43:41,580 --> 00:43:43,290
Your grandfather.

704
00:43:43,415 --> 00:43:48,295
And he loved her more
than life itself.

705
00:43:48,921 --> 00:43:54,885
But they were from different
worlds and couldn't be together.

706
00:43:57,387 --> 00:44:00,182
How did she die, Mr. Gracey?

707
00:44:00,307 --> 00:44:02,392
She took her own life.

708
00:44:02,518 --> 00:44:04,102
Poison.

709
00:44:04,186 --> 00:44:08,106
After that, his life
became unbearable.

710
00:44:08,190 --> 00:44:13,111
And so, without
hope, without love,

711
00:44:13,195 --> 00:44:16,281
without Elizabeth,

712
00:44:16,406 --> 00:44:18,700
he hung himself.

713
00:44:20,285 --> 00:44:26,792
His soul wanders these halls,
waiting for her to return.

714
00:44:29,503 --> 00:44:32,381
If you listen carefully,

715
00:44:32,506 --> 00:44:38,679
you can still hear the
beating of his broken heart.

716
00:44:47,688 --> 00:44:49,273
Wait a minute. Hold it a second.

717
00:44:49,314 --> 00:44:50,816
You're telling me
this guy is dead

718
00:44:50,899 --> 00:44:52,260
and the reason we
were brought here

719
00:44:52,317 --> 00:44:54,194
is he wants to try to
get jiggy with my wife?

720
00:44:54,236 --> 00:44:56,780
Pretty much. Are you upset?

721
00:44:56,905 --> 00:44:59,616
The guy is dead, and he's
trying to get with my wife!

722
00:44:59,658 --> 00:45:01,118
And the house isn't
really for sale!

723
00:45:01,201 --> 00:45:03,161
Yes, I'm upset!

724
00:45:03,203 --> 00:45:06,290
Oh, Madame Leota, is it her?

725
00:45:06,415 --> 00:45:10,210
Is she truly our dear, departed
Elizabeth come back to us?

726
00:45:10,252 --> 00:45:13,213
It is true. She
walks these halls.

727
00:45:13,297 --> 00:45:15,299
You see? I told you it is her!

728
00:45:15,340 --> 00:45:17,551
But do not be deceived.

729
00:45:17,593 --> 00:45:20,304
All things are not
as they appear.

730
00:45:20,512 --> 00:45:23,765
For the curse to be lifted,
the truth must be known.

731
00:45:23,807 --> 00:45:27,019
And for the truth to be
known, you must find the key.

732
00:45:27,102 --> 00:45:29,188
What are you talking about, ball lady?
What key?

733
00:45:29,229 --> 00:45:31,815
Enter the tomb under
the great dead oak

734
00:45:31,899 --> 00:45:34,401
and travel down deep
under the ground.

735
00:45:34,484 --> 00:45:37,779
And there you will find
the key that must be found.

736
00:45:37,905 --> 00:45:40,699
Find the black crypt
that bears no name,

737
00:45:40,782 --> 00:45:43,619
or soon your fate
will be the same.

738
00:45:43,702 --> 00:45:45,746
You're telling me all I
have to do is find this key,

739
00:45:45,787 --> 00:45:47,907
then I'm gonna walk out of
here with my wife and kids?

740
00:45:47,931 --> 00:45:50,751
The key is the answer to all.

741
00:45:50,792 --> 00:45:52,711
Well, great. I'm in.
Let's get this key.

742
00:45:52,794 --> 00:45:54,588
There's only one problem.

743
00:45:54,713 --> 00:45:56,298
How do we get out of here?

744
00:45:56,381 --> 00:45:58,300
Yeah, how do we get out of here?

745
00:45:58,383 --> 00:46:04,014
Well, there's
always, uh, my way.

746
00:46:10,521 --> 00:46:13,524
Hey! I thought you said
you could drive this thing!

747
00:46:13,607 --> 00:46:16,026
Don't you worry. I know
exactly what I'm doing.

748
00:46:17,110 --> 00:46:18,695
- Aah!
- Aah!

749
00:46:21,406 --> 00:46:23,617
Well, you better just keep
your eyes on the road!

750
00:46:23,659 --> 00:46:25,285
- Move over!
- What are you doing?

751
00:46:25,327 --> 00:46:27,412
If you keep driving,
you'll kill us all!

752
00:46:27,496 --> 00:46:28,622
That's where you're wrong.

753
00:46:28,705 --> 00:46:30,499
Because some of us
are already dead!

754
00:46:36,213 --> 00:46:37,798
Dad, look.

755
00:46:55,232 --> 00:46:58,026
Ready? Fire!

756
00:47:14,186 --> 00:47:15,186
Dad?

757
00:47:15,210 --> 00:47:15,961
Yes, son?

758
00:47:16,003 --> 00:47:18,505
I see dead people.

759
00:47:24,720 --> 00:47:25,971
Excuse me.

760
00:47:26,013 --> 00:47:28,307
Why are all these ghosts
still hanging around here?

761
00:47:28,432 --> 00:47:30,726
When they died, they
couldn't find the light.

762
00:47:30,809 --> 00:47:32,269
And now...

763
00:47:32,311 --> 00:47:34,229
Now they're trapped.

764
00:47:34,313 --> 00:47:38,108
Doomed to wander the
Earth for all eternity.

765
00:47:41,904 --> 00:47:44,323
Nice. Nice job.

766
00:47:57,711 --> 00:47:59,421
Whoa!

767
00:48:00,797 --> 00:48:02,090
Okay.

768
00:48:02,174 --> 00:48:03,425
Hey!

769
00:48:03,509 --> 00:48:05,302
Hey, what are you doing here?

770
00:48:05,427 --> 00:48:06,929
Can they see us?

771
