I am a rational man.

1027
01:01:44,329 --> 01:01:46,915
It was my responsibility
to the house.

1028
01:01:46,999 --> 01:01:49,001
My duty, sir, to see to it

1029
01:01:49,126 --> 01:01:53,213
that the boy did not make a
foolish error in judgment.

1030
01:01:53,297 --> 01:01:57,634
Running away with that girl
would have destroyed this house.

1031
01:01:57,676 --> 01:01:59,720
It would have
destroyed everything.

1032
01:01:59,803 --> 01:02:03,515
And I could not stand by and
watch it all fall to ruin.

1033
01:02:03,557 --> 01:02:05,017
Punch his face in, Dad.

1034
01:02:05,100 --> 01:02:07,728
Yeah, but first I'm gonna tell
his master what really happened.

1035
01:02:07,769 --> 01:02:09,521
The master must never know.

1036
01:02:09,605 --> 01:02:12,316
Edward and his love
will be reunited,

1037
01:02:12,399 --> 01:02:14,318
and this curse will be broken.

1038
01:02:14,401 --> 01:02:15,861
That's not her. That's my wife.

1039
01:02:15,903 --> 01:02:18,530
And what she sees in
you I'll never know.

1040
01:02:18,614 --> 01:02:21,033
But that is of little
importance now.

1041
01:02:21,116 --> 01:02:25,412
The only thing that matters is
that the master's pain must end.

1042
01:02:25,454 --> 01:02:27,706
And it will end tonight.

1043
01:02:27,831 --> 01:02:32,211
The curse will be broken, and
we can all finally move on.

1044
01:02:32,294 --> 01:02:35,005
All right. That's it, man.
Where's my wife?

1045
01:02:35,130 --> 01:02:37,132
Getting ready for her
wedding, of course.

1046
01:02:37,216 --> 01:02:38,509
What wedding? He
can't marry her.

1047
01:02:38,634 --> 01:02:39,927
He's dead, and she's not.

1048
01:02:40,010 --> 01:02:41,386
True.

1049
01:02:41,428 --> 01:02:43,889
But that can be
easily corrected.

1050
01:02:43,931 --> 01:02:48,227
Life, I'm afraid, is
such a delicate state.

1051
01:02:48,310 --> 01:02:51,730
If you put one finger on my
wife, I swear I'll kill you.

1052
01:02:54,733 --> 01:02:58,403
How wonderful. You're
going to kill a ghost.

1053
01:02:58,445 --> 01:03:00,614
- Leave him alone!
- Stop it!

1054
01:03:02,199 --> 01:03:03,909
- Aah!
- Aah!

1055
01:03:04,034 --> 01:03:06,119
Let them go!

1056
01:03:09,706 --> 01:03:12,334
You're gonna let my kids out
of here, take me to my wife,

1057
01:03:12,417 --> 01:03:13,919
and let us out of
here right now!

1058
01:03:14,002 --> 01:03:17,798
You want out, fine.

1059
01:03:17,923 --> 01:03:20,801
Let me show you out.

1060
01:03:24,304 --> 01:03:29,434
Now, for the last time,
good night, Mr. Evers.

1061
01:03:31,103 --> 01:03:33,522
Aah!

1062
01:03:33,605 --> 01:03:35,315
Ugh!

1063
01:03:42,698 --> 01:03:44,700
Oh!

1064
01:04:05,721 --> 01:04:08,015
This house has waited so long

1065
01:04:08,098 --> 01:04:11,894
to have its shroud
of darkness lifted.

1066
01:04:12,019 --> 01:04:18,734
And tonight, for the first
time in, oh, so many years,

1067
01:04:18,775 --> 01:04:20,527
I believe it may be possible

1068
01:04:20,611 --> 01:04:25,115
that the story will
finally end differently.

1069
01:04:25,157 --> 01:04:26,825
Sara?

1070
01:04:26,909 --> 01:04:30,329
Do you believe that love
is about second chances?

1071
01:04:30,412 --> 01:04:32,831
About forgiveness?

1072
01:04:32,915 --> 01:04:35,626
Yes, I do.

1073
01:04:36,126 --> 01:04:38,128
Don't you remember?

1074
01:04:38,212 --> 01:04:39,671
Remember?

1075
01:04:39,713 --> 01:04:41,215
Mr. Gracey, are you all right?

1076
01:04:41,298 --> 01:04:43,133
Don't you recognize me at all?

1077
01:04:43,217 --> 01:04:44,635
Mr. Gracey.

1078
01:04:44,718 --> 01:04:47,012
I thought certainly bringing
you back to Gracey Manor

1079
01:04:47,095 --> 01:04:48,889
would help you remember.

1080
01:04:48,931 --> 01:04:51,308
Remember what? Mr. Gracey,
you're scaring me.

1081
01:04:51,433 --> 01:04:53,227
Where it happened.

1082
01:04:53,310 --> 01:04:55,354
Where we spent our
last moments together.

1083
01:04:55,395 --> 01:04:58,899
Where we danced together for
the last time before you...

1084
01:04:58,941 --> 01:05:00,817
Before you killed yourself!

1085
01:05:00,859 --> 01:05:02,694
But now you've returned to me.

1086
01:05:02,819 --> 01:05:05,531
And at long last,
we can be together.

1087
01:05:05,614 --> 01:05:07,115
Why do you not remember?

1088
01:05:07,199 --> 01:05:09,159
You were my world, my life!

1089
01:05:09,201 --> 01:05:11,912
And I have loved you in
death as I did in life!

1090
01:05:11,995 --> 01:05:13,664
Let me go!

1091
01:05:13,705 --> 01:05:15,916
Why do you not remember?

1092
01:05:17,918 --> 01:05:19,920
You are her. You are Elizabeth.

1093
01:05:20,003 --> 01:05:21,129
You must be!

1094
01:05:21,213 --> 01:05:23,215
Can you not sense it?
Search your heart.

1095
01:05:23,257 --> 01:05:24,800
I am your one true love.

1096
01:05:24,925 --> 01:05:26,301
And now we can
finally be together.

1097
01:05:26,426 --> 01:05:27,594
Don't you understand?

1098
01:05:28,095 --> 01:05:29,721
Elizabeth, you
must listen to me.

1099
01:05:29,763 --> 01:05:31,181
I'm not Elizabeth!

1100
01:05:31,223 --> 01:05:33,183
Please! I implore you.

1101
01:05:33,225 --> 01:05:35,811
Leave me alone!
Get away from me!

1102
01:05:41,608 --> 01:05:44,528
She doesn't remember.

1103
01:05:44,611 --> 01:05:46,029
It can't be her.

1104
01:05:46,113 --> 01:05:48,365
It is her, sir.

1105
01:05:48,407 --> 01:05:51,702
The gypsy woman
prophesied her return.

1106
01:05:51,827 --> 01:05:54,705
And now the time has come.

1107
01:05:55,414 --> 01:05:56,915
You had best get ready.

1108
01:05:56,999 --> 01:05:58,917
But she doesn't remember.

1109
01:05:59,001 --> 01:06:01,628
In time she will, sir.

1110
01:06:01,712 --> 01:06:05,007
I assure you she will.

1111
01:06:10,220 --> 01:06:13,807
Open up! Hey!

1112
01:06:13,932 --> 01:06:15,809
Let me in!

1113
01:06:28,822 --> 01:06:30,908
Aah!

1114
01:06:48,133 --> 01:06:50,511
Oh, Ramsley, you
have to help me.

1115
01:06:50,594 --> 01:06:53,430
There's something horribly wrong.
Mr. Gracey...

1116
01:06:53,472 --> 01:06:56,433
Yes. I know, my dear. I know.

1117
01:06:56,475 --> 01:06:58,018
He's expecting you.

1118
01:06:58,101 --> 01:07:01,813
He's always been expecting you.

1119
01:07:01,897 --> 01:07:04,816
And you haven't put
on your dress yet.

1120
01:07:04,900 --> 01:07:07,402
We can't keep the
master waiting.

1121
01:07:07,528 --> 01:07:09,321
Waiting? For what?

1122
01:07:09,404 --> 01:07:12,699
Why, your wedding, of course.

1123
01:07:12,824 --> 01:07:13,909
My...

1124
01:07:14,535 --> 01:07:16,453
I'm not Elizabeth!

1125
01:07:16,495 --> 01:07:18,330
Of course you are, my dear.

1126
01:07:18,413 --> 01:07:19,915
You may not see it yet.

1127
01:07:19,998 --> 01:07:22,209
But in time you will.

1128
01:07:22,334 --> 01:07:25,420
You don't actually think I'm
going through with this madness?

1129
01:07:25,504 --> 01:07:28,924
Oh, yes. I very much do.

1130
01:07:29,007 --> 01:07:30,717
You see...

1131
01:07:30,801 --> 01:07:33,804
we wouldn't want anything
to happen to the children.

1132
01:07:33,929 --> 01:07:35,806
Now, would we?

1133
01:07:35,931 --> 01:07:37,724
Michael! Megan!

1134
01:07:37,766 --> 01:07:39,518
You wouldn't.

1135
01:07:39,601 --> 01:07:41,603
Of course not, my dear.

1136
01:07:41,728 --> 01:07:43,814
But that is entirely up to you.

1137
01:07:43,897 --> 01:07:50,404
If not, I really do
fear for the children.

1138
01:07:53,407 --> 01:07:55,033
Have her ready.

1139
01:07:55,117 --> 01:07:58,704
And this time, any further
acts of insubordination

1140
01:07:58,829 --> 01:08:01,623
will be dealt with in the
harshest possible manner.

1141
01:08:01,707 --> 01:08:03,458
But, sir?

1142
01:08:03,500 --> 01:08:06,795
There are worse things
than purgatory, madam.

1143
01:08:06,920 --> 01:08:09,298
I can assure you.

1144
01:08:12,426 --> 01:08:14,595
Have her ready.

1145
01:08:57,221 --> 01:09:00,224
Tears of joy.

1146
01:09:24,206 --> 01:09:26,124
What are you doing?

1147
01:09:26,208 --> 01:09:28,460
Hey, you leave me alone.

1148
01:09:28,502 --> 01:09:30,212
Just get out of here
and leave me alone.

1149
01:09:30,295 --> 01:09:30,963
Oh, I see.

1150
01:09:31,004 --> 01:09:34,007
You're just gonna sit there,
feeling sorry for yourself.

1151
01:09:34,132 --> 01:09:35,926
You tell me why not.

1152
01:09:36,009 --> 01:09:38,512
This whole thing was my fault.

1153
01:09:38,595 --> 01:09:41,431
We should've never been
here in the first place.

1154
01:09:41,515 --> 01:09:43,183
Supposed to be at the lake.

1155
01:09:43,225 --> 01:09:47,020
We'd be sitting by a
warm fire right now.

1156
01:09:47,062 --> 01:09:49,523
And I made us come here.

1157
01:09:49,606 --> 01:09:52,401
And now it's too late.

1158
01:09:52,526 --> 01:09:55,320
No. It's never too late.

1159
01:09:55,404 --> 01:09:58,198
Hey, look, I tried to get in
there, and I can't, all right?

1160
01:09:58,240 --> 01:09:59,950
I tried! I failed!

1161
01:09:59,992 --> 01:10:03,662
You try. You fail.

1162
01:10:03,704 --> 01:10:07,416
But the only true failure
is when you stop trying.

1163
01:10:07,499 --> 01:10:10,794
What do you want me to do? Huh?

1164
01:10:12,504 --> 01:10:14,715
Try again.

1165
01:10:21,013 --> 01:10:22,014
Hold on!

1166
01:10:22,097 --> 01:10:24,308
With what?

1167
01:10:30,230 --> 01:10:32,733
- Aah!
- Aah!

1168
01:10:36,320 --> 01:10:38,030
Elizabeth?

1169
01:10:41,700 --> 01:10:44,328
Yes, my love.

1170
01:10:51,126 --> 01:10:52,211
I'll be right back.

1171
01:10:52,294 --> 01:10:55,130
Okay. I'll wait here.

1172
01:10:57,132 --> 01:10:58,592
Dearly beloved,

1173
01:10:58,634 --> 01:11:01,428
we are gathered together
here in the sight of God

1174
01:11:01,512 --> 01:11:04,932
to join this man and this woman
in the bonds of holy matrimony.

1175
01:11:05,015 --> 01:11:07,809
Dad! Help us!

1176
01:11:09,895 --> 01:11:12,606
Michael! Megan!

1177
01:11:15,817 --> 01:11:18,320
Wilt thou, Edward Gracey,

1178
01:11:18,403 --> 01:11:20,906
have this woman to
be thy wedded wife,

1179
01:11:21,031 --> 01:11:23,534
to live together
after God's ordinance

1180
01:11:23,617 --> 01:11:25,827
in the holiest
state of matrimony?

1181
01:11:25,869 --> 01:11:27,120
I will.

1182
01:11:31,124 --> 01:11:34,711
And do you, Elizabeth Henshaw,

1183
01:11:34,795 --> 01:11:37,589
take this man to be
your lawful husband,

1184
01:11:37,631 --> 01:11:43,220
to love and cherish in
death as you did in life?

1185
01:11:43,303 --> 01:11:44,303
I do.

1186
01:11:44,596 --> 01:11:46,014
Whoa!

1187
01:11:52,312 --> 01:11:54,606
Aah!

1188
01:11:55,023 --> 01:11:59,027
From this day forward, you
shall be joined together as one

1189
01:11:59,111 --> 01:12:03,323
for all eternity until
the very end of time.

1190
01:12:10,914 --> 01:12:16,295
What God has joined together
let no man cast asunder.

1191
01:12:19,923 --> 01:12:21,508
- Dad!
- Dad!

1192
01:12:23,802 --> 01:12:27,014
If anyone has any objections...

1193
01:12:29,016 --> 01:12:31,602
Yeah, I got a few objections!

1194
01:12:37,900 --> 01:12:39,693
The next time I say
we're going to the lake,

1195
01:12:39,818 --> 01:12:42,112
- we're going to the lake.
- Let's go.

1196
01:12:43,530 --> 01:12:45,115
Get away from her.

1197
01:12:45,199 --> 01:12:46,700
I lost her once.

1198
01:12:46,825 --> 01:12:48,952
I don't intend to
let it happen again.

1199
01:12:48,994 --> 01:12:51,622
This is not Elizabeth. Ramsley,
you tell him the truth.

1200
01:12:51,705 --> 01:12:54,708
I don't know what
you're talking about.

1201
01:12:54,833 --> 01:12:55,918
Now you got amnesia, huh?

1202
01:12:56,001 --> 01:12:58,003
Elizabeth didn't kill herself.
He did it.

1203
01:12:58,128 --> 01:12:59,630
He's been lying
to you all along.

1204
01:12:59,713 --> 01:13:02,132
I'm warning you, sir.

1205
01:13:02,216 --> 01:13:03,258
Step away.

1206
01:13:03,300 --> 01:13:04,941
Don't think 'cause you
pull out your sword

1207
01:13:05,010 --> 01:13:06,290
I'm gonna let you marry my wife.

1208
01:13:06,314 --> 01:13:08,472
My patience is wearing thin.

1209
01:13:08,514 --> 01:13:10,724
Elizabeth, please, come along.

1210
01:13:10,766 --> 01:13:13,393
I'm not Elizabeth.

1211
01:13:13,519 --> 01:13:14,394
You must be.

1212
01:13:14,520 --> 01:13:16,605
Her name is Sara.
She's from New Jersey.

1213
01:13:16,730 --> 01:13:18,371
Ramsley wants you to
think she's Elizabeth

1214
01:13:18,398 --> 01:13:20,317
so this curse would be lifted.

1215
01:13:20,400 --> 01:13:22,528
That is absurd.

1216
01:13:22,611 --> 01:13:24,154
Forgive me.

1217
01:13:24,196 --> 01:13:25,531
If you're gonna
kill me, kill me.

1218
01:13:25,614 --> 01:13:27,115
But on the other side,

1219
01:13:27,199 --> 01:13:29,079
I'm gonna be whipping
your ass for all eternity.

1220
01:13:29,103 --> 01:13:31,620
So maybe you should read this
before you stab somebody.

1221
01:13:31,703 --> 01:13:33,830
- What is it?
- It's Elizabeth's letter.

1222
01:13:33,914 --> 01:13:35,415
Her real letter.
The one she wrote.

1223
01:13:35,499 --> 01:13:38,126
The one he stole.
You never saw it.

1224
01:13:46,134 --> 01:13:48,387
What's the meaning of this?

1225
01:13:48,428 --> 01:13:52,724
Must we continue to listen to
the ramblings of a lunatic?

1226
01:13:52,808 --> 01:13:54,518
But it is written in her hand.

1227
01:13:54,601 --> 01:13:57,020
Yeah, it's written in her hand.
Explain that, Ramsley.

1228
01:13:57,104 --> 01:13:58,897
Well?

1229
01:14:03,193 --> 01:14:06,154
Your union was unacceptable.

1230
01:14:06,196 --> 01:14:10,617
I tried to warn you,
but you wouldn't listen.

1231
01:14:10,659 --> 01:14:12,160
So you killed her.

1232
01:14:12,202 --> 01:14:16,206
I told you it would be a mistake
to run away with that girl.

1233
01:14:16,248 --> 01:14:19,626
But I loved her!
Was love my mistake?

1234
01:14:19,668 --> 01:14:21,295
Yes!

1235
01:14:21,920 --> 01:14:23,881
I tried to protect you.

1236
01:14:23,922 --> 01:14:27,801
All these years I've
sacrificed for you.

1237
01:14:27,926 --> 01:14:32,514
But what would you understand
of sacrifice, duty, or honor?

1238
01:14:32,598 --> 01:14:34,516
You loved her.

1239
01:14:34,600 --> 01:14:36,435
Well, damn you.

1240
01:14:36,518 --> 01:14:39,021
Damn you all to hell!

1241
01:14:44,401 --> 01:14:46,528
Aah!

1242
01:15:18,727 --> 01:15:20,729
Aah!

1243
01:15:23,375 --> 01:15:24,375
Aah!

1244
01:15:24,399 --> 01:15:26,109
Jim!

1245
01:15:26,151 --> 01:15:27,819
Aah!

1246
01:15:29,821 --> 01:15:32,199
Aah!

1247
01:15:37,204 --> 01:15:39,122
Aah!

1248
01:15:59,810 --> 01:16:02,020
- Mom!
- Mom!

1249
01:16:02,104 --> 01:16:03,105
Mom, what's wrong?

1250
01:16:03,230 --> 01:16:04,314
Are you all right?

1251
01:16:04,398 --> 01:16:05,816
- Mom.
- Hey!

1252
01:16:05,899 --> 01:16:08,193
Hey, Sara. Sara,
what's the matter?

1253
01:16:08,318 --> 01:16:10,362
Sara, what's wrong?

1254
01:16:10,404 --> 01:16:12,030
Hey, what's the matter?
What's wrong?

1255
01:16:12,114 --> 01:16:13,907
It's the poison!

1256
01:16:14,032 --> 01:16:15,117
Oh, no.

1257
01:16:15,200 --> 01:16:17,327
No. Hey, Sara.

1258
01:16:17,411 --> 01:16:18,829
Come on. Please. Don't do this!

1259
01:16:18,912 --> 01:16:20,330
Sara, don't do this. Please.

1260
01:16:20,414 --> 01:16:22,124
Jim...

1261
01:16:23,333 --> 01:16:25,586
Sara! Hey!

1262
01:16:25,627 --> 01:16:27,921
Sara. Sara, come on. Please.

1263
01:16:27,963 --> 01:16:29,423
Sara.

1264
01:16:29,506 --> 01:16:31,300
Sara, I love you.

1265
01:16:31,425 --> 01:16:34,303
Sara, please.
I love you so much.

1266
01:16:41,435 --> 01:16:43,312
Hey, get away from us!
Leave us alone!

1267
01:16:43,395 --> 01:16:44,521
No, Dad.

1268
01:16:44,605 --> 01:16:46,523
It won't hurt us.

1269
01:17:55,133 --> 01:17:57,594
Elizabeth, is that you?

1270
01:17:57,719 --> 01:18:00,097
Yes, my love.

1271
01:18:00,222 --> 01:18:03,100
The ghost ball was Elizabeth.

1272
01:18:03,225 --> 01:18:06,603
The truth had to be known
for me to be released.

1273
01:18:06,728 --> 01:18:09,231
He saved me.

1274
01:18:11,024 --> 01:18:13,569
It was nothing.

1275
01:18:13,610 --> 01:18:15,988
Oh, Elizabeth.

1276
01:18:16,029 --> 01:18:18,323
Yes, my darling?

1277
01:18:19,324 --> 01:18:23,412
I have waited so
long for this moment.

1278
01:18:23,495 --> 01:18:26,623
And now only heaven awaits.

1279
01:18:37,718 --> 01:18:40,429
He's not really
kissing your mom.

1280
01:18:44,725 --> 01:18:46,226
Hey.

1281
01:18:47,519 --> 01:18:49,396
That's my wife.

1282
01:18:58,113 --> 01:18:59,531
Sara?

1283
01:19:06,496 --> 01:19:07,998
Jim?

1284
01:19:08,123 --> 01:19:09,917
I thought I lost you.

1285
01:19:09,958 --> 01:19:11,502
